{{Infobox church | name = Church of St. Denis | fullname = | other name = | native_name = Collégiale Saint-Denis en Liège | native_name_lang = fr | image = Jan Weissenbruch - De kerk van St Denis te Luik.jpg | imagesize = | imagelink = | imagealt = | caption = [[Jan Weissenbruch]], ''The Church of St. Denis in Liège'' (about 1850-1860) | pushpin map = Belgium | pushpin label position = | pushpin map alt = | pushpin mapsize = | relief = | map caption = | coordinates = {{coord|50|38|34.57|N|5|34|28.51|E|display=inline,title}} | iso region = | location = Place Saint-Denis, [[Liège]] | country = [[Belgium]] | denomination = [[Catholic Church]] | attendance = | website = {{URL|http://www.upsl.be/communautes/paroissiales/saint-denis/}} | former name = | bull date = | founded date = 978 | founder = [[Notker of Liège]] | dedication = | dedicated date = | consecrated date = 12 March 990 | cult = | relics = | events = | past bishop = | people = | status = | functional status = parish church | heritage designation = Patrimoine exceptionnel | designated date = 1936 | architect = | architectural type = | style = [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] | years built = | groundbreaking = | completed date = | construction cost = | closed date = | demolished date = | capacity = | length = <!-- {{convert| }} --> | width = <!-- {{convert| }} --> | width nave = <!-- {{convert| }} --> | height = <!-- {{convert| }} --> | diameter = <!-- {{convert| }} --> | other dimensions = | floor count = | floor area = <!-- {{convert| }} --> | spire quantity = | spire height = <!-- {{convert| }} --> | materials = | bells = | bells hung = | bell weight = <!-- {{long ton|0| }} --> | parish = Unité pastorale Saint-Lambert | deanery = | archdeaconry = | episcopalarea = | archdiocese = | metropolis = | diocese = [[Diocese of Liège]] | province = | bishop = [[Jean-Pierre Delville]] | dean = | provost = | canon = | priestincharge = | priest = | asstpriest = | deacon = | seniorpastor = | pastor = | sacristan = | organistdom = | director = | organist = | businessmgr = | liturgycoord = | reledu = | rcia = | youthmin = | flowerguild = | musicgroup = | parishadmin = | serversguild = | logo = | logosize = | logolink = | logoalt = | embedded = }} The '''Church of St. Denis''' ({{lang-fr|Collégiale Saint-Denis}}) in [[Liège]], [[Belgium]], is a former [[fortified church|fortified]] [[collegiate church]], founded by [[Notker of Liège]] in 987 and first consecrated on 12 March 990.<ref>Theodose Bouille, ''Histoire de la ville et pays de Liege'', [https://books.google.es/books?id=4xtUAAAAcAAJ vol. 1] (Liège, 1725), p. 75.</ref> The tower was added around 1100. The church has since 1936 been registered as a listed building, and is currently listed as "exceptional heritage" of [[Wallonia]].<ref>[http://spw.wallonie.be/dgo4/site_ipic/index.php/fiche/fiche?codeInt=62063-INV-0341-02 Heritage listing] accessed 22 Feb. 2015.</ref>
==History== The Church of St Denis was one of the [[seven collegiate churches of Liège]], which until the [[Liège Revolution]] of 1789 collectively comprised the "secondary clergy" in the [[First Estate]] of the [[Prince-bishopric of Liège]]. The church was suppressed in 1797, but the building was taken into use as a parish church in 1803.<ref>[http://spw.wallonie.be/dgo4/site_ipic/index.php/fiche/fiche?codeInt=62063-INV-0341-02 Heritage listing] accessed 22 Feb. 2015.</ref>
