{{Infobox organization |logo = |name = FIGMA |type = [[Non-profit organization|Non-profit]], [[self-regulatory organization|self-regulatory]] |formation = {{Start date and age|1999}} |location = {{nowrap|[[Helsinki]], Finland}} |area_served = Finland |key_people = |purpose = [[Video game ratings|Rating of video game content]] |parent_organization = |homepage = }}
FIGMA or Finnish Games and Multimedia Association was founded in 1999. It is the Finnish equivalent to [[Entertainment Software Rating Board]]. Which regulates video game content in relation to subjects such as sex and violence and assigns age appropriate certificates.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.v2.fi/uutiset/pelit/10037/FIGMA-ratsasi-taas-alaikaisille-kiellettyja-peleja-myyvat-liikkeet/|title=FIGMA ratsasi taas alaikäisille kiellettyjä pelejä myyvät liikkeet|website=www.v2.fi|accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://visionist.fi/2011/11/04/figma-ry-uusi-webbisivustonsa-ja-visuaalisen-ilmeensa/|title=FIGMA ry uusi webbisivustonsa ja visuaalisen ilmeensä|date=4 November 2011|publisher=|accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mynewsdesk.com/fi/pressreleases/maailman-suurimmilla-pelimessuilla-oli-ennaetysyleisoe-673134|title=Maailman suurimmilla pelimessuilla oli ennätysyleisö|publisher=|accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref>
Figma publishes the best-selling video games every two weeks, and gives out platinum and gold prizes, its keeps yearly statistics on the size of the Finnish video game market, and organizes the [[Finnish Game Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neogames.fi/fga2014eng/|title=The Finnish Game Awards honoured the best in the Finnish game industry - Neogames|website=www.neogames.fi|accessdate=13 October 2018}}</ref>
