{{Infobox person | name = Iram Parveen Bilal | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Iram Parveen Bilal | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Nigeria]], Pakistan | residence = Los Angeles, California | alma_mater = [[California Institute of Technology]], [[University of Southern California]] | occupation = [[Filmmaker]] | years_active = | known_for = ''[[Josh: Independence Through Unity]] (film)'' | home_town = | notable_works = | spouse = | website = <!-- {{http://www.iramparveenbilal.com|Iram Parveen Bilal}} --> }}
'''Iram Parveen Bilal''' is an international filmmaker and entrepreneur. In 2012 her first feature film [[Josh: Independence Through Unity]] debuted at the [[Mumbai Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography|url=http://www.iramparveenbilal.com/biography.html|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>
==Early life== Bilal was raised in [[Nigeria]] and [[Pakistan]], she came to America to study at the [[California Institute of Technology]]. She graduated with her B.S, honors, in Environmental Science Engineering. Upon graduating, Bilal was awarded a unique opportunity with the [[Thomas J. Watson Fellowship]], a travel fellowship grant that took her around the world.<ref name=Caltech>{{cite web|title=Caltech Alumni|url=http://www.alumni.caltech.edu/news/2014/iram-parveen-bilal|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>
She was the inspiration behind [[Kareena Kapoor]]’s character name in the movie [[Agent Vinod (2012 film)|Agent Vinod]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Meet-the-real-Iram-Parveen-Bilal/articleshow/12481590.cms|title=Meet the real Iram Parveen Bilal - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2017-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thereviewmonk.com/article/ushering-new-wave-pakistani-cinema-iram-parveen-bilal/|title=Ushering in the New-Wave of Pakistani Cinema: Iram Parveen Bilal - The Review Monk|work=The Review Monk|access-date=2017-09-15|language=en-US}}</ref>
==Career==
===Filmmaker=== Bilal began her career in film by getting her M.F.A. at the prestigious Peter Stark Producing Program at the [[University of Southern California]]. Her most recent film [[Josh: Independence Through Unity]] is a mystery thriller set in Karachi that follows an upper class woman who becomes determined to find out what happened to her missing caretaker. Her journey takes her to a nearby village run by a feudal lord, and in the process endangers herself and others. The story tackles themes of feudalism, youth movements, poverty, and the challenges of trying to do good amidst social unrest.<ref name=Caltech/>
Other feature projects in development have received attention by [[Independent Filmmaker Project|IFP]], The Academy’s Nicholl Writing Fellowship, Mumbai Sankalan Lab, Film Independent and Women In Film. Prominent awards and honors include the Thomas J. Watson Fellowship, Stark Special Project Scholarship,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://iffr.com/en/persons/iram-parveen-bilal|title=Iram Parveen Bilal|date=2015-09-04|work=IFFR|access-date=2017-09-15|language=en}}</ref> Mabel Beckman Leadership Award, Paul Studenski Fellowship and the Dean’s Cup. In March 2013, she was asked to give a TedX talk entitled "Get Uncomfortable Now" at Caltech.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ted Conferences|url=http://tedxtalks.ted.com/video/Get-Uncomfortable-Now-Iram-Parv|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>
===Qalambaaz=== In 2014 Bilal initialed Qalambaaz, a platform that provides mentors and nurtures the growth of screenplay writers through competition. The screenplay writing competition was recently launched at The Second Floor (T2F) under Bilal's banner Parveen Shah Productions.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Story Exchange|url=http://thestoryexchange.org/iram-parveen-bilal/|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref> Bilal clarifies that the platform does not promise funding for filmmakers, but guarantees a final product that can be sold as a possible feature film production.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Qamar|first1=Saadia|title=Qalambaaz: In search of the perfect screenplay|url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/751764/qalambaaz-in-search-of-the-perfect-screenplay/|accessdate=11 January 2015}}</ref>
